commit.message:
theme: add doom-oksolar-{dark,light}

These themes are a variation on Solarized based on a new theory of color
perception called OKLab. A description of the themes by the author can
be found at https://meat.io/oksolar.

The implementation in this commit is based on the `doom-solarized`
themes, with the following differences:

- in the dark theme, `region` is set to `base1` instead of `base0`
  because otherwise it is indistinguishable from the background.
- in the light theme, `hl-line` has a background of `base1` instead of
  `base3` because otherwise syntax highlight mixes with background.

Also in this commit:

- adjust base colors, region and bg of code blocks
- adjust base colors after reading how they are intended for Solarized (see 
  https://ethanschoonover.com/solarized/#usage-development).
- fix the `region` colour picked from the base palette to get a
  better highlighted line in Vertico, Helm and other completion engines.
- tweaked the background of Markdown code blocks explicitly, so
  that they don't clash too much with syntax highlighting.
- adjust base palette for light theme
- darken instead of brighten Markdown code blocks.

Ref: https://meat.io/oksolar
Ref: https://ethanschoonover.com/solarized/#usage-development
